text: State Route 248 (SR 248) is an east–west secondary state highway located entirely in Williamson County in Middle Tennessee. ==Route description== SR 248 begins at an interchange-style junction with U.S. Route 31 (US 31, SR 6) near Thompson’s Station, and goes northeast through rural areas to have an intersection with U.S. Route 431 (US 431, SR 106) before it comes to an end at Interstate 65 (I-65) southeast of Franklin. After the I-65 junction near the Williamson County Fairgrounds, the road continues as Peytonsville Road, a locally maintained thoroughfare connecting the interchange with the town of Peytonsville and I-840. ==Major intersections== ==References== 248 248
title: Tennessee State Route 248
